<AbstractNarration>0088940&lt;br/&gt;Haxton&lt;br/&gt;This project will allow the continuation of the national&lt;br/&gt;Summer School in Nuclear Physics, now in its 12th year, for &lt;br/&gt;an additional five years.  This annual school is intended for&lt;br/&gt;advanced graduate students and beginning postdoctoral &lt;br/&gt;researchers in theory or experiment, and consists of several&lt;br/&gt;courses of introductory lectures by leading nuclear physicists.&lt;br/&gt;One main goal is to provide nuclear physics students with a&lt;br/&gt;broad perspective on the field, thereby combating the &lt;br/&gt;specialization that often occurs within focused research&lt;br/&gt;groups.  NSF funding for the school covers the expenses&lt;br/&gt;of the lecturers and a portion of the local costs of the&lt;br/&gt;students who attend.  More information on this year's school&lt;br/&gt;can be found at http://int.phys.washington.edu/NPSS/NPSS.html.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
